1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on learning a policy for an intelligent agent to approach an object in an indoor environment, which is a core problem in robotics. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses visual inputs (depth and semantic segmentation) to learn the approaching policy, which is a key aspect of computer vision. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents a novel solution for learning a generalizable approaching policy, which is a core problem in AI. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses machine learning techniques to learn the approaching policy from visual inputs. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with controlling an intelligent agent to approach an object in an indoor environment, which is a core problem in systems and control.
